From 36da34aaed2a85b9db0d40b78261adf1f0d033a9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: YTing46 <q36141367@gs.ncku.edu.tw>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 04:50:02 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 13/19] riscv: dts: sophgo: duo256m: clock sec_sys syscon
 accesses with clk_efuse

Any load/store to the SEC_SYS block (0x020b0000) with clk_efuse
(CLK_EN_0 bit 11) gated stalls the AXI interconnect and wedges the
whole SoC, including MMC - a single devmem read is enough to
reproduce. Mainline gates the unused clock at late_initcall via
clk_disable_unused, so the first C906L remoteproc start after boot
(sysfs 'echo start') froze all rootfs I/O board-wide.

The vendor kernel avoids this by wrapping every sec_top access in
clk_prepare_enable(clk_efuse) (cvitek-spacc.c). Do the equivalent
declaratively: give the sec_sys syscon node a clocks property so
syscon attaches clk_efuse to the regmap and regmap-mmio enables it
just-in-time around each access.

Verified on Duo256M: with the clock gated (hw enable = N), rproc
start/stop/start all return 0, rpmsg pingpong RTT ~155us, and the
gate drops back to N when idle. Replaces the clk_ignore_unused
cmdline workaround.

---
 arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
index bb129d9843da..bacf88f6b874 100644
--- a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
+++ b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/sophgo/sg2002-milkv-duo256m.dts
@@ -63,10 +63,19 @@ soc {
 		 * SEC_SYS block: C906L enable (0x04 bit13) and boot address
 		 * (0x20/0x24), same registers the vendor FSBL pokes to start
 		 * the little core (fsbl/plat/cv181x/platform.c).
+		 *
+		 * Register access requires clk_efuse (CLK_EN_0 bit 11): with
+		 * it gated, any load/store to this block stalls the bus and
+		 * wedges the whole SoC (vendor cvitek-spacc.c wraps its
+		 * sec_top pokes in clk_prepare_enable(clk_efuse) for the same
+		 * reason). syscon attaches the clock to the regmap so every
+		 * access enables it just-in-time, surviving
+		 * clk_disable_unused without clk_ignore_unused.
 		 */
 		sec_sys: syscon@20b0000 {
 			compatible = "sophgo,sg2002-sec-sys", "syscon";
 			reg = <0x020b0000 0x1000>;
+			clocks = <&clk CLK_EFUSE>;
 		};
 	};
 
